Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into 1-inch-thick pieces. Trim and thinly slice @Persian cucumber{1} into rounds. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{½%cup}, ¾ cup water, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> For 4 servings: Use 1 1/2 cups water.

While rice cooks, toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of oil. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until tender and golden brown at edges, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #large bowl{}, combine half the @rice wine vinegar{1.7%ounce}, @sugar{1%tsp}, and @Sriracha{2%teaspoon} to taste; stir to dissolve sugar. Add @coleslaw mix{4%ounce} and season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat.

In a #small bowl{}, combine remaining vinegar, @sugar{½%tsp}, and @Korean chili flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste; stir to dissolve sugar. Add cucumber and stir to coat.

Set both bowls aside, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

> For 4 servings: Use 2 tsp sugar in slaw and 1 tsp sugar in pickled cucumber.

Pat @sirloin steak{14%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @bulgogi sauce{4%ounce} and 1 TBSP water. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring, until warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat.

> For 4 servings: Use 2 TBSP butter and 2 TBSP water.

> TIP: If sauce is too thick, stir in a splash of water.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

Thinly slice steak against the grain.

Divide rice, steak, and carrots between plates. Spoon sauce over steak and sprinkle with scallion greens. Serve with individual bowls of kimchi-style slaw and pickled cucumber on the side.

> For 4 servings: Use 2 TBSP butter.